1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 4262 By: Johns
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to teachers; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 6-204.2, as amended by Section 1, Chapter
8 374, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 6-
204.2), which relates to the Education Leadership
9 Oklahoma program; updating Commission name; providing
for annual bonus for teachers with National Board
10 certification; removing reference to additional
salary increment; amending Section 1, Chapter 289,
11 O.S.L. 2023, as last amended by Section 2, Chapter
480, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 18-
12 114.15), which relates to the minimum salary
schedule; striking National Board certification
13 salary increment; providing an effective date; and
declaring an emergency.
14
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 6-204.2, as
19 amended by Section 1, Chapter 374, O.S.L. 2025 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
20 Section 6-204.2), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 6-204.2. A. The Commission for Educational Quality and
22 Accountability and the State Board of Education are authorized to
23 establish the Education Leadership Oklahoma program.
24
Req. No. 15206 Page 1

1 B. The purposes of the Education Leadership Oklahoma program
2 are to:
3 1. Provide teachers throughout the state information about
4 National Board certification and the Education Leadership Oklahoma
5 program services;
6 2. Provide technical assistance and National-Board-certified
7 mentors to all teachers seeking National Board certification upon
8 request;
9 3. Reward teachers who are seeking National Board certification
10 by awarding them a portion of the National Board certification cost
11 as provided in subsection D of this section; and
12 4. Provide recognition to National-Board-certified teachers.
13 C. To fulfill the objectives of the Education Leadership
14 Oklahoma Act, the Oklahoma Commission for Teacher Preparation
15 Educational Quality and Accountability shall:
16 1. Inform teachers of the Education Leadership Oklahoma program
17 and services it provides to teachers seeking National Board
18 certification, emphasizing recruiting efforts toward teachers at
19 high-poverty schools, schools identified as in need of improvement
20 and in districts with the lowest percentage of teachers who have
21 achieved National Board certification; and
22 2. Ensure that all teachers seeking National Board
23 certification receive adequate information regarding the level of
24 commitment required to acquire National Board certification.
Req. No. 15206 Page 2

1 D. The Commission shall select not more than one hundred
2 applicants to participate in the program each fiscal year for whom
3 the Commission shall pay up to One Thousand Eight Hundred Dollars
4 ($1,800.00) per applicant of the National Board certification cost.
5 E. The Commission shall promulgate rules establishing a process
6 for accepting applications for the Education Leadership Oklahoma
7 program and for providing to applicants selected for the program up-
8 front payment of the National Board certification cost. If a
9 selected applicant who receives the up-front payment does not
10 fulfill all submission requirements for National Board certification
11 as established by the certification vendor within the maximum
12 allowable time frame, the applicant will be required to repay the
13 full amount of the component fees paid on his or her behalf, the
14 applicant shall repay the Commission the full amount paid by the
15 Commission pursuant to subsection D of this section. Subject to the
16 availability of funding, all selected applicants who do not receive
17 an up-front payment and successfully complete National Board
18 certification shall be reimbursed by the Commission for the National
19 Board certification cost. The total amount of reimbursement paid by
20 the Commission shall not exceed One Thousand Eight Hundred Dollars
21 ($1,800.00) per applicant.
22 F. Subject to the availability of funding, all teachers seeking
23 initial National Board certification either through the Education
24 Leadership Oklahoma Scholarship program or paying their own way
Req. No. 15206 Page 3

1 shal l be eligible to participate in Education Leadership Oklahoma
2 mentoring for up to three (3) years to assist them in meeting the
3 requirements of the National Board certification process, free of
4 charge.
5 G. Subject to district board of education policy or collective
6 bargaining agreement, additional professional leave days may be
7 granted to teachers seeking National Board certification for
8 National Board certification portfolio development. During the two
9 (2) days of the additional professional days granted to teachers for
10 National Board certification portfolio development, a substitute
11 teacher shall be provided by the school district at no cost to the
12 teacher.
13 H. 1. The State Board of Education shall provide to teachers
14 who attained National Board certification prior to June 30, 2013, a
15 bonus in the amount of Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00) annually
16 over a ten-year period, to be paid no later than January 31 each
17 year. The Beginning July 1, 2026, the Board shall provide a bonus
18 in the amount of Five Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00) annually over a
19 five-year period, to be paid no later than January 31 each year to
20 any teacher who:
21 a. attains National Board certification after June 30,
22 2013, if the teacher was selected for the Education
23 Leadership Oklahoma program before June 30, 2013, or
24 the teacher has submitted an application for National
Req. No. 15206 Page 4

1 Board certification to the National Board for
2 Professional Teaching Standards before June 30, 2013
3 July 1, 2026,
4 b. attained National Board certification before July 1,
5 2026, and was receiving a bonus in the amount of Five
6 Thousand Dollars ($5,000.00) annually, for the
7 remaining time of the ten-year period, or
8 c. attained National Board certification before July 1,
9 2026, and was receiving an additional salary increment
10 pursuant to the minimum salary schedule in Section 18-
11 114.15 of this title, for the remaining time of the
12 ten-year period.
13 2. The teachers eligible to receive the annual bonus as
14 provided for in paragraph 1 of this subsection shall receive the
15 annual bonus for the ten-year five-year duration of their National
16 Board certification or for the remaining duration of their National
17 Board certification if the teachers attained National Board
18 certification before July 1, 2026, and has less than ten (10) years
19 remaining in their certification and so long as they are teaching in
20 the classroom full-time in an Oklahoma public school. No school or
21 school district shall be liable for payment of bonuses pursuant to
22 this section. The bonus shall be funded by state dollars from the
23 lottery funds as provided for Section 713 of Title 3A and shall be
24 paid directly to eligible teachers through school districts.
Req. No. 15206 Page 5

1 3. The bonus shall not be included in the calculation of the
2 teacher's salary for purposes of meeting the district or statutory
3 minimum salary schedule or for purposes of compensating Oklahoma
4 Teachers' Retirement System contributions or benefits.
5 4. Teachers eligible to receive the annual bonus as provided
6 for in paragraph 1 of this subsection shall not be eligible to
7 receive the additional salary increment for National Board
8 certification as set forth in the minimum salary schedule in Section
9 18-114.15 of this title.
10 5. Teachers who attain National Board certification after June
11 30, 2013, shall be eligible to receive the additional salary
12 increments for National Board certification as set forth in the
13 minimum salary schedule in Section 18-114.15 of this title.
14 6. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules for a
15 process by which a National-Board-certified teacher will verify
16 that:
17 a. the National Board certification has not lapsed,
18 b. the teacher is still a full-time teacher, and
19 c. for teachers eligible for the bonus, the teacher has
20 not exceeded the limit of annual bonus payments as
21 provided for in paragraph 1 of this subsection.
22 I. It is the intent of the Legislature that the Oklahoma State
23 Regents for Higher Education incorporate the National Board
24
Req. No. 15206 Page 6

1 cert ification portfolio development into all programs in education
2 leading to a master's level degree.
